aV<p>This is what happens when you use variable name of negative meaning, you need to invert their values.  The following would be easier to understand:</p>\u000a\u000a<pre><code>sorted = False\u000awhile not sorted:\u000a    ...\u000a</code></pre>\u000a\u000a<p>On the other hand, the logic of the algorithm is a little bit off.  You need to check whether two elements swapped during the for loop.  Here's how I would write it:</p>\u000a\u000a<pre><code>def bubble(values):\u000a    length = len(values) - 1\u000a    sorted = False\u000a    while not sorted:\u000a        sorted = True\u000a        for element in range(0,length):\u000a            if values[element] &gt; values[element + 1]:\u000a                 hold = values[element + 1]\u000a                 values[element + 1] = values[element]\u000a                 values[element] = hold\u000a                 sorted = False\u000a    return values\u000a</code></pre>\u000a
